public enum AppState
extends java.lang.Enum<AppState>

Enum describing the state of the MMF app. Possible values are:

  • APP_NOT_INSTALLED
  • NOT_LOGGED_IN
  • NOT_RECORDING
  • RECORDING
  • RECORDING_PAUSED
  • POST_RECORDING

Enum Constant Summary

          The app is not currently connected to the MMF app

NOT_RECORDING
          The user is logged into the app, but the app is not in a recording state.

          The workout was stopped, but it has yet to be saved or discarded.

APP_NOT_CONNECTED

The app is not currently connected to the MMF app

APP_NOT_INSTALLED

public static final AppState APP_NOT_INSTALLED
A companion MMF app has not been installed on the device. At this time, we support:
  • MapMyRun
  • MapMyRun+
  • MapMyRide
  • MapMyRide+
  • MapMyWalk
  • MapMyWalk+
  • MapMyHike
  • MapMyHike+
  • MapMyFitness

NOT_LOGGED_IN

public static final AppState NOT_LOGGED_IN
The user is not logged into the app. Before any other action can be taken he must be prompted to login.

NOT_RECORDING

public static final AppState NOT_RECORDING
The user is logged into the app, but the app is not in a recording state. At this state the app is ready to begin a recording.

RECORDING

public static final AppState RECORDING
The app is currently recording a workout.

RECORDING_PAUSED

public static final AppState RECORDING_PAUSED
The app is paused, but in a recording state. The workout can not be stopped or resummed.

POST_RECORDING

public static final AppState POST_RECORDING
The workout was stopped, but it has yet to be saved or discarded. Once it is saved or discarded it will go back to the NOT_RECORDING state.
